==Bare machine computing==


'''Bare Machine Computing''' ('''BMC''') is a computing paradigm in which application software runs directly on a [[bare machine]]. In the BMC paradigm, the application software is a single, stand-alone executable that runs without an [[operating system]] (OS) or device drivers. The application software has direct access to hardware resources, and there is typically no distinction between user and kernel mode. It is self-managed software that boots, loads and runs without using any other software components. BMC systems have no OS-related vulnerabilities, and thus have improved security over OS-based systems.
